text: Kozhay-Semyonovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Kozhay-Semyonovsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 590 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 21 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Kozhay-Semyonovka
